Why NFS?

	Network File System (NFS) allows a system to share directories and files with others over a network.
	
What does an NFS server do?

	NFS servers export directories. 
	
What does an NFS client do?

	NFS clients can mount the exported directories on their local machine.
	
	How?
			1. Manually via the mount command
			2. Persistently: /etc/fstab
			3. Automounter!
				1) Which we will soon learn about.
			
		Must install nfs-utils package first.
		

